article_title: Former Virginia Sen. Jim Webb Starts 2016 Presidential Chase
article_text:
Former Democratic Sen. Jim Webb of Virginia is the first official 2016 presidential candidate.

Mr. Webb, 68 years old, announced an exploratory committee late Wednesday for what would be a long shot campaign, with a 14-minute video and a 2,100-word letter posted to his website. He served as Navy secretary under President Ronald Reagan and was elected to the Senate in 2006 as an antiwar conservative Democrat, defeating Republican...
